Everton have bolstered manager Carlo Ancelotti’s backroom
staff with the appointment of sports performance manager Mino Fulco. According to The Athletic, Fulco who is Ancelotti’s son-in-law is set to take over the reins of Bruno Mendes who was in the same role under former manager Marco Silva. READ ALSO:  Breaking: Quique Setién becomes Barcelona new head coach The 34-year-old previously worked with Ancelotti at Bayern
Munich, Real Madrid and Napoli – the appointment comes as no surprise. Fulco will be working alongside Duncan Ferguson and Davide
Ancelotti as well as Francesco Mauri who is the Head of Fitness. Everton will make the trip to West Ham United on Saturday,
January 18 as they look to secure a win and climb up the Premier League table.